article.headline: Bethune-Cookman 64, Norfolk St. 57
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. -- Jarrell Thomas scored 14 points to lead Bethune-Cookman past Norfolk State 64-57 on Saturday. Bethune-Cookman (12-11, 6-3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference) had lost consecutive games, but outscored the Spartans 12-5 in the final 6:19 to break a tie and split the season series. Tobias Mahone and Alexander Starling hit consecutive baskets, giving the Wildcats a 56-52 lead with 4:36 left. Michael DeLoach's two free throws cut Bethune-Cookman's lead to 57-55 with 2:30 remaining, but the Wildcats scored the next five points for a 62-55 advantage with 49 seconds left. Norfolk State (7-13, 5-4) shot only 38 percent from the field (19 of 50). John Holmes scored 13 points and C.J. Reed added 12 points for the Wildcats. Deloach scored 18 points, Corey Lyons had 13 and Joseph Dorsett-Jeffreys 12 for Norfolk State. Brandon Monroe had 14 rebounds.
